request: This information is regarding the reist of seizures with antipsychotic agents, with emphasis on the long-acting depot agents (fluphenazine, haloperidol, aripiprazole, olanzapine, paliperidone, and risperidone). A 66 year-old female with a history of schizophrenia and an unspecified seizure hisotry previously treat with haloperidol decanoate was admitted for delirium and seizures. She requires therapy for her schizophrenia and the use of a long-acting depot injection is preferable.
